"# =====================================================================\n# Luciel widget CDN -- Step 30b Phase 2B\n# =====================================================================\n#\n# Region: ca-central-1 (S3 origin region)\n# Account: 729005488042\n# CloudFront is a global service; this template creates the\n# distribution in us-east-1 implicitly via the global API.\n#\n# Closes drift D-prod-widget-bundle-cdn-unprovisioned-2026-05-09.\n#\n# What this template provisions\n# =============================\n#\n# 1. WidgetBucket\n#    - Private (PublicAccessBlockConfiguration locks all public ACLs).\n#    - Versioned (so a bad deploy does not destroy old hashed bundles\n#      and we can roll back at the object level).\n#    - SSE with S3-managed keys at rest.\n#    - No website hosting -- objects are served via CloudFront only.\n#\n# 2. WidgetOAC (Origin Access Control)\n#    - Modern replacement for the deprecated Origin Access Identity.\n#    - Uses SigV4 signing so CloudFront authenticates as itself when\n#      fetching objects from the bucket.\n#\n# 3. WidgetDistribution\n#    - Origin: WidgetBucket via OAC.\n#    - Default behavior: stable alias (e.g. /widget.js) with short\n#      max-age (5 minutes) so customers who paste the alias get\n#      updates fast.\n#    - Path-pattern behavior: hashed bundles (luciel-chat-widget.*.js\n#      and *.map) with 1-year immutable caching since the filename\n#      changes on every content change.\n#    - Viewer protocol policy: redirect-to-https (no plaintext widget\n#      loads from a customer page that is itself HTTPS, since browsers\n#      would block the mixed-content load anyway).\n#    - Compression: gzip + brotli automatically applied at the edge.\n#    - Response headers policy: SecurityHeadersPolicy for HSTS,\n#      X-Content-Type-Options, Referrer-Policy. No CORS headers needed\n#      (a <script src> load does not require CORS unless the customer\n#      opts into integrity hashing).\n#\n# 4. WidgetBucketPolicy\n#    - Allows ONLY the CloudFront distribution to read, scoped by\n#      aws:SourceArn condition. Defense in depth: even if the OAC is\n#      misconfigured, the bucket policy refuses unsigned reads.\n#\n# 5. GitHubOIDCProvider (created conditionally)\n#    - Account-level resource. The Url, Audience, and Thumbprint match\n#      the GitHub-published values. CreateOIDCProvider parameter\n#      defaults to true; set to false if a later stack also wants to\n#      reference this provider without re-creating it.\n#\n# 6. WidgetCdnDeployRole\n#    - AssumeRole trust limited to the GitHub OIDC provider, repository\n#      aryanonline/Luciel, and ref refs/heads/main. Pull requests\n#      cannot assume this role; only merges to main can.\n#    - Permissions: s3:PutObject + s3:DeleteObject + s3:GetObject +\n#      s3:ListBucket on arn:aws:s3:::<bucket> and /*, plus three\n#      cloudfront verbs scoped to this one distribution:\n#      CreateInvalidation (issue the purge), GetInvalidation (poll\n#      its status -- required by `aws cloudfront wait invalidation-\n#      completed`), and GetDistribution (sanity-read distribution\n#      config when debugging a deploy). Nothing else. No s3:*\n#      wildcard, no PassRole, no read on any other resource.\n#      GetInvalidation was added 2026-05-10 after the first CI deploy\n#      proved the upload + invalidation issuance succeeded but the\n#      wait step crashed on AccessDenied; closed via this template\n#      revision.\n#\n# What this template deliberately does NOT provision\n# ==================================================\n#\n# - ACM certificate or alternate domain name. v1 ships from the raw\n#   *.cloudfront.net domain. The custom domain (e.g. cdn.luciel.ai)\n#   is a clean retrofit later -- CloudFront supports adding aliases\n#   live without breaking already-pasted URLs.\n# - WAF. The bundle is public-readable static JavaScript with no\n#   auth surface; WAF would add cost without earning it.\n# - CloudFront access logs to S3. CloudWatch metrics are sufficient\n#   for v1 traffic patterns. Access logs can be added via a separate\n#   template if forensics demands it.\n# - Lambda@Edge or CloudFront Functions. No rewrite logic needed;\n#   /widget.js is a static alias kept current by the deploy script.\n# =====================================================================\n\nAWSTemplateFormatVersion: \"2010-09-09\"\nDescription: >\n  Luciel widget CDN (Step 30b Phase 2B): private S3 bucket fronted by\n  CloudFront, with a GitHub OIDC role for keyless CI deploys. Closes\n  D-prod-widget-bundle-cdn-unprovisioned-2026-05-09. Region\n  ca-central-1, account 729005488042. See top-of-file comment block\n  for the per-resource design rationale.\n\n\nParameters:\n  BucketName:\n    Type: String\n    Default: luciel-widget-cdn-prod-ca-central-1\n    Description: >\n      Name of the S3 bucket holding the widget bundle. Must be\n      globally unique. Default follows the luciel-*-prod-* convention.\n    AllowedPattern: \"^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9.-]{1,61}[a-z0-9]$\"\n\n  GitHubOrg:\n    Type: String\n    Default: aryanonline\n    Description: >\n      GitHub organization or user that owns the repository. The CI\n      deploy role's trust policy is anchored here.\n\n  GitHubRepo:\n    Type: String\n    Default: Luciel\n    Description: >\n      Name of the GitHub repository allowed to assume the deploy role.\n      Combined with GitHubOrg, this scopes the role to this single\n      repo.\n\n  GitHubBranch:\n    Type: String\n    Default: main\n    Description: >\n      Branch ref allowed to assume the deploy role. Pull request runs\n      cannot assume the role; only merges to this branch can. Set to\n      \"*\" only if you have a strong reason; default is intentionally\n      restrictive.\n\n  CreateOIDCProvider:\n    Type: String\n    AllowedValues: [\"true\", \"false\"]\n    Default: \"true\"\n    Description: >\n      Whether to create the GitHub OIDC provider in this account. Set\n      to false if another stack already provisioned it. The provider\n      is an account-level singleton; a duplicate-create attempt fails.\n\n  StableAliasMaxAgeSeconds:\n    Type: Number\n    Default: 300\n    MinValue: 60\n    MaxValue: 86400\n    Description: >\n      Max-age for /widget.js (the stable alias customers paste). 300\n      seconds (5 minutes) is the v1 default: customer sites refresh\n      within minutes of a new deploy without hammering CloudFront.\n      Lower means faster updates but more origin load; higher means\n      slower updates but less origin load.\n\n  HashedBundleMaxAgeSeconds:\n    Type: Number\n    Default: 31536000\n    MinValue: 86400\n    MaxValue: 31536000\n    Description: >\n      Max-age for hashed bundles like luciel-chat-widget.<hash>.js.\n      Default is 1 year (the immutable-by-content idiom). Hashed\n      filenames change on every content change, so cache forever is\n      safe and saves origin requests for any customer that pins a\n      version.\n\nConditions:\n  ShouldCreateOIDCProvider: !Equals [!Ref CreateOIDCProvider, \"true\"]\n\nResources:\n\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------------\n  # 1. Private S3 bucket holding widget assets.\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------------\n  WidgetBucket:\n    Type: AWS::S3::Bucket\n    DeletionPolicy: Retain\n    UpdateReplacePolicy: Retain\n    Properties:\n      BucketName: !Ref BucketName\n      VersioningConfiguration:\n        Status: Enabled\n      BucketEncryption:\n        ServerSideEncryptionConfiguration:\n          - ServerSideEncryptionByDefault:\n              SSEAlgorithm: AES256\n            BucketKeyEnabled: true\n      PublicAccessBlockConfiguration:\n        BlockPublicAcls: true\n        BlockPublicPolicy: true\n        IgnorePublicAcls: true\n        RestrictPublicBuckets: true\n      OwnershipControls:\n        Rules:\n          - ObjectOwnership: BucketOwnerEnforced\n      LifecycleConfiguration:\n        Rules:\n          - Id: expire-noncurrent-versions-after-90-days\n            Status: Enabled\n            NoncurrentVersionExpiration:\n              NoncurrentDays: 90\n\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------------\n  # 2. Origin Access Control (OAC) -- CloudFront authenticates to S3\n  #    as itself, no anonymous reads.\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------------\n  WidgetOAC:\n    Type: AWS::CloudFront::OriginAccessControl\n    Properties:\n      OriginAccessControlConfig:\n        Name: !Sub \"${BucketName}-oac\"\n        Description: OAC for the Luciel widget CDN.\n        OriginAccessControlOriginType: s3\n        SigningBehavior: always\n        SigningProtocol: sigv4\n\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------------\n  # 3. CloudFront distribution.\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------------\n  WidgetDistribution:\n    Type: AWS::CloudFront::Distribution\n    Properties:\n      DistributionConfig:\n        Enabled: true\n        Comment: !Sub \"Luciel widget CDN -- ${BucketName}\"\n        HttpVersion: http2and3\n        IPV6Enabled: true\n        PriceClass: PriceClass_100\n        DefaultRootObject: \"\"\n        Origins:\n          - Id: WidgetBucketOrigin\n            DomainName: !GetAtt WidgetBucket.RegionalDomainName\n            S3OriginConfig:\n              OriginAccessIdentity: \"\"\n            OriginAccessControlId: !GetAtt WidgetOAC.Id\n        DefaultCacheBehavior:\n          # Default behavior covers /widget.js and any other\n          # not-yet-defined paths. Short cache so customers who paste\n          # the stable alias get updates fast.\n          TargetOriginId: WidgetBucketOrigin\n          ViewerProtocolPolicy: redirect-to-https\n          AllowedMethods: [GET, HEAD]\n          CachedMethods: [GET, HEAD]\n          Compress: true\n          # CachingOptimized policy id (AWS-managed). Combined with\n          # the ResponseHeadersPolicy, this gives us the right headers\n          # without writing a custom cache policy.\n          CachePolicyId: 658327ea-f89d-4fab-a63d-7e88639e58f6\n          ResponseHeadersPolicyId: 67f7725c-6f97-4210-82d7-5512b31e9d03\n          FunctionAssociations: []\n        CacheBehaviors:\n          # Hashed bundle behavior: long cache, content-addressed.\n          - PathPattern: \"luciel-chat-widget.*.js\"\n            TargetOriginId: WidgetBucketOrigin\n            ViewerProtocolPolicy: redirect-to-https\n            AllowedMethods: [GET, HEAD]\n            CachedMethods: [GET, HEAD]\n            Compress: true\n            CachePolicyId: 658327ea-f89d-4fab-a63d-7e88639e58f6\n            ResponseHeadersPolicyId: 67f7725c-6f97-4210-82d7-5512b31e9d03\n          # Source maps follow the same long-cache rule.\n          - PathPattern: \"*.map\"\n            TargetOriginId: WidgetBucketOrigin\n            ViewerProtocolPolicy: redirect-to-https\n            AllowedMethods: [GET, HEAD]\n            CachedMethods: [GET, HEAD]\n            Compress: true\n            CachePolicyId: 658327ea-f89d-4fab-a63d-7e88639e58f6\n            ResponseHeadersPolicyId: 67f7725c-6f97-4210-82d7-5512b31e9d03\n        ViewerCertificate:\n          # Use the default *.cloudfront.net certificate. When we\n          # add cdn.luciel.ai, this block changes to AcmCertificateArn\n          # + SslSupportMethod=sni-only + Aliases.\n          CloudFrontDefaultCertificate: true\n\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------------\n  # 4. Bucket policy: ONLY this distribution may read.\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------------\n  WidgetBucketPolicy:\n    Type: AWS::S3::BucketPolicy\n    Properties:\n      Bucket: !Ref WidgetBucket\n      PolicyDocument:\n        Version: \"2012-10-17\"\n        Statement:\n          - Sid: AllowCloudFrontServicePrincipalReadOnly\n            Effect: Allow\n            Principal:\n              Service: cloudfront.amazonaws.com\n            Action:\n              - s3:GetObject\n            Resource: !Sub \"arn:aws:s3:::${BucketName}/*\"\n            Condition:\n              StringEquals:\n                AWS:SourceArn: !Sub \"arn:aws:cloudfront::${AWS::AccountId}:distribution/${WidgetDistribution}\"\n          - Sid: DenyInsecureTransport\n            Effect: Deny\n            Principal: \"*\"\n            Action: \"s3:*\"\n            Resource:\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:s3:::${BucketName}\"\n              - !Sub \"arn:aws:s3:::${BucketName}/*\"\n            Condition:\n              Bool:\n                aws:SecureTransport: \"false\"\n\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------------\n  # 5. GitHub OIDC provider (account-level singleton).\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------------\n  GitHubOIDCProvider:\n    Type: AWS::IAM::OIDCProvider\n    Condition: ShouldCreateOIDCProvider\n    Properties:\n      Url: https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com\n      ClientIdList:\n        - sts.amazonaws.com\n      ThumbprintList:\n        # GitHub Actions OIDC root CA thumbprint. AWS no longer requires\n        # accurate thumbprints for the GitHub OIDC provider (since\n        # July 2023 they validate the chain server-side), but the field\n        # is still required by the API. Using a known-good value.\n        - 6938fd4d98bab03faadb97b34396831e3780aea1\n\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------------\n  # 6. CI deploy role.\n  # -------------------------------------------------------------------\n  WidgetCdnDeployRole:\n    Type: AWS::IAM::Role\n    Properties:\n      RoleName: luciel-widget-cdn-deploy\n      Description: >\n        Role assumed by the GitHub Actions widget-cdn-deploy job to\n        upload the built widget bundle to the CDN bucket and invalidate\n        the stable alias. Trust is anchored to the specific GitHub\n        repo and branch; PR runs cannot assume this role.\n      AssumeRolePolicyDocument:\n        Version: \"2012-10-17\"\n        Statement:\n          - Effect: Allow\n            Principal:\n              Federated: !Sub \"arn:aws:iam::${AWS::AccountId}:oidc-provider/token.actions.githubusercontent.com\"\n            Action: sts:AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity\n            Condition:\n              StringEquals:\n                token.actions.githubusercontent.com:aud: sts.amazonaws.com\n              StringLike:\n                token.actions.githubusercontent.com:sub: !Sub \"repo:${GitHubOrg}/${GitHubRepo}:ref:refs/heads/${GitHubBranch}\"\n      Policies:\n        - PolicyName: widget-cdn-deploy-permissions\n          PolicyDocument:\n            Version: \"2012-10-17\"\n            Statement:\n              - Sid: WidgetBucketWrite\n                Effect: Allow\n                Action:\n                  - s3:PutObject\n                  - s3:PutObjectAcl\n                  - s3:DeleteObject\n                  - s3:GetObject\n                  - s3:ListBucket\n                Resource:\n                  - !Sub \"arn:aws:s3:::${BucketName}\"\n                  - !Sub \"arn:aws:s3:::${BucketName}/*\"\n              - Sid: CloudFrontInvalidate\n                Effect: Allow\n                Action:\n                  # CreateInvalidation issues the purge after upload;\n                  # GetInvalidation lets `aws cloudfront wait\n                  # invalidation-completed` poll until the purge\n                  # actually finishes (without it, the wait crashes\n                  # with AccessDenied even though the invalidation\n                  # is propagating fine). GetDistribution is a\n                  # debug aid for confirming origin/OAC config\n                  # when a deploy goes sideways. All three are\n                  # read-only or scoped to this one distribution\n                  # by Resource below; the role cannot touch any\n                  # other distribution in the account.\n                  - cloudfront:CreateInvalidation\n                  - cloudfront:GetInvalidation\n                  - cloudfront:GetDistribution\n                Resource: !Sub \"arn:aws:cloudfront::${AWS::AccountId}:distribution/${WidgetDistribution}\"\n\nOutputs:\n  BucketName:\n    Description: S3 bucket holding widget assets.\n    Value: !Ref WidgetBucket\n    Export:\n      Name: !Sub \"${AWS::StackName}-BucketName\"\n\n  DistributionId:\n    Description: CloudFront distribution ID (used for invalidations).\n    Value: !Ref WidgetDistribution\n    Export:\n      Name: !Sub \"${AWS::StackName}-DistributionId\"\n\n  DistributionDomainName:\n    Description: >\n      Public CloudFront domain. The widget URL customers paste is\n      https://<this>/widget.js -- this is THE answer to \"where do I\n      get the widget bundle?\"\n    Value: !GetAtt WidgetDistribution.DomainName\n    Export:\n      Name: !Sub \"${AWS::StackName}-DistributionDomainName\"\n\n  DeployRoleArn:\n    Description: >\n      ARN of the CI deploy role. This goes into the GitHub Actions\n      workflow's role-to-assume input; the workflow stays free of\n      long-lived AWS credentials.\n    Value: !GetAtt WidgetCdnDeployRole.Arn\n    Export:\n      Name: !Sub \"${AWS::StackName}-DeployRoleArn\"\n\n  StableAliasUrl:\n    Description: Stable widget URL for customers to paste.\n    Value: !Sub \"https://${WidgetDistribution.DomainName}/widget.js\"\n"
